{"key":"processedPost-9391714","value":{"id":9391714,"first":9391266,"last":9553281,"when":1228762420,"utime":"12/08/08 08:53 PM","content":"Don't heat your terrarium.&nbsp; As has been said for years, doing so causes condensation on the sides, and that condensation is made by robbing humidity from the air in your terrarium.<br />You'll have to heat the area your terrarium is sitting in.&nbsp; While <i>you</i> may like the cold, your mushrooms are a tropical species and they won't.&nbsp; Find a way to get the ambient temperature where your terrarium sits to 70F to 75F.<br />RR","title":"Re: First Grow, Terrarium Question"}}